Marketing Brief -- Central Newspapers Inc.:
   Interest Is Sold by Father
   Of Vice President Quayle
Vice President Quayle owns 27,800 shares of the company's
Class A common stock and 25,000 shares of Class B, according
to his most recent financial-disclosure statement. The market
value of his holdings is about $1.1 million, based on
yesterday's New York Stock Exchange closing price of $21.75 a
share.
   Neither the elder Mr. Quayle nor the vice president, who
was returning from a trip to Europe, could be reached for
comment. A vice presidential spokesman said the transaction
didn't involve the vice president or his holdings.